               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origDate calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1800" notBefore="1700">Dated to 1743 by Vinson in Vinson et al. (1866-) on the basis of the colophone. Dated to 1743 by Cabaton (1912), on unstated grounds. There are several internal dates in the manuscript, but it is not clear if these are dates of copy or dates copied from the master copy, if any.</origDate>
                     
                  <origPlace>Tamilnadu.</origPlace></origin>
                  <provenance><p>Unknown.</p></provenance>
                  <acquisition><p>According to cabaton this is the <ref target="https://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/btv1b105278700/f17">Bible</ref> and <ref target="https://gallica.bnf.fr/ark:/12148/btv1b105278700/f31">Bible en Malabar ou Tamoul</ref> sent by the Jesuits of the Mission du Carnate in 1729 for the library of the king of France and mentioned in ancien lists (BnF NAF 5442, f5r and f9r), which he dates to 1743 though. Those lists however state this Bible, as well as two other manuscripts, are printed editions by the Lutheran missionnaries from Tranquebar.</p></acquisition>
